        purchased - the date of purchase
        type - the type of the bike

        price - the price of the bike
        type - the type for the bike
        batteryPercentage - the battery percentage of the bike
        distanceTraveled - how far the bike has traveled
        location - the location of the bike
        status - the status of the bike
        purchased - the date of purchase date of the bike
        totalTrips - the number of trips the bike has had.

      • addRepairRequest

        public boolean addRepairRequest(java.lang.String desc,
                                java.time.LocalDate date)
        addRepairRequest takes the parameters given and creates a new Repair object. It also takes the Repair object and register it to the database directly through the startRepairRequest method in the Repair Object.
        Parameters:
        desc - the description of the problem
        date - the date of register
        Returns:
        a boolean based on the results given by the DBH object. If it got registered to the DB it returns true, otherwise it returns false

      • finishLastRepairRequest

        public boolean finishLastRepairRequest(java.lang.String returnDesc,
                                       java.time.LocalDate returnDate,
                                       double price)
        finishLastRepairRequest takes the parameters given and finishes the last Repair object in the Repair object array. It also register it to the database through finishRepairRequest method in the Repair object.
        Parameters:
        returnDesc - the description of the fixed bike
        returnDate - the date of return
        price - the cost of the repair
        Returns:
        a boolean based on results from DBH. True = Finished request, False = Not finished request
